I hung the new nest box during the day. Here's how it looks in the garden.
However, let's briefly revisit it. It seems no one has asked, "What's inside?"
At the top is an ESP32 camera board with a fisheye lens camera, and an infrared LED light that I removed from a Raspberry Pi camera.
The plastic box has an unusual shape because the side panels of the nest box can rotate. When I bought it, it was like this and couldn't be modified, so I had to design according to this situation.
Since there's no power supply in the garden, the entire device is powered by a solar panel and a 2600mAh 18650 lithium-ion battery.
I didn't take pictures of the battery or charger, but here is a picture of the solar panel.
The battery is stored in a gray box on the side of the nest box.
Fully charged, it can run for about 4 hours.
I call this a "niche feature." This way, the birds get a bit of personal space too.
